labelClaimList.name: EU_LOW_ENERGY
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is low in energy, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains more than 40 kcal (170 kJ) / 100 g in the solids or more than 20kcal (80kJ) / 100 ml in the case of liquids. For table-top sweeteners the limit of 4 kcal (17 kJ) / portion, with equivalent sweetening properties to 6g of sucrose (approximately 1 teaspoon of sucrose), applies.

labelClaimList.name: EU_FREE_FROM_ENERGY
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is energy-free, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains more than 4 kcal (17 kJ) / 100 ml. For table-top sweeteners the limit of 0,4 kcal (1,7 kJ) / portion, with equivalent sweetening properties to 6g of sucrose (approximately 1 teaspoon of sucrose), applies.

labelClaimList.name: EU_LOW_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is low in fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 3g of fat per 100 g in the case of solids or 1,5 g fat per 100 ml in the case of liquid (1.8 g fat per 100 ml for semi-skimmed milk).

labelClaimList.name: EU_FREE_FROM_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food does not contain fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 0.5g of fat per 100 g or 100 ml. However, claims expressed as "X% fat free" are prohibited.

labelClaimList.name: EU_LOW_SATURATED_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is low in saturated fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the sum of saturated fatty acids and trans fatty acids in product is not greater than 1.5 g per 100 g for solids or 0,75 g per 100 ml of liquid, the sum of saturated fatty acids and trans fatty acids that can not produce, in both cases, more 10% of the energy.

labelClaimList.name: EU_FREE_FROM_SATURATED_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food does not contain saturated fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the sum of saturated fatty acids and trans fatty acids does not exceed 0.1g saturated fat per 100g or per 100ml.

labelClaimList.name: EU_FREE_FROM_SUGARS
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food contains no sugars, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 0.5g of sugars per 100g or 100 ml.

labelClaimList.name: NO_ADDED_SUGARS
labelClaimList.description: A claim that has not been added sugars in a food, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product does not contain any added mono- or disaccharides or any other food used for its sweetening properties. If sugars are naturally present in food, the following indication should also appear on the label: "CONTAINS NATURALLY OCCURRING SUGARS".

labelClaimList.name: EU_LOW_SODIUM_SALT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is low in sodium or salt, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 0.12g of sodium, or the equivalent value for salt, per 100g or per 100ml. Regarding the waters, other than natural mineral waters, this value should not exceed 2 mg of sodium per 100 ml.

labelClaimList.name: EU_VERY_LOW_SODIUM_SALT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is very low in sodium or salt, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 0.04g of sodium or the equivalent value for salt, per 100g or 100ml. It is prohibited to use this claim for natural mineral waters and other waters.

labelClaimList.name: EU_FREE_FROM_SODIUM_SALT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food does not contain sodium or salt, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains no more than 0.005 g of sodium or equivalent salt per 100 g.

labelClaimList.name: EU_SOURCE_OF_FIBRE
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is a source of fiber, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains at least 3g of fiber per 100g or at least 1 5 g of fiber per 100 kcal.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_FIBRE
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in fiber, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains at least 6g of fiber per 100g or at least 3g of fiber per 100 kcal.

labelClaimList.name: EU_SOURCE_OF_PROTEIN
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is a source of protein, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where at least 12% of the energy value of the food is provided by proteins.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_PROTEIN
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in protein, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where at least 20% of the energy value of the food is provided by protein .

labelClaimList.name: EU_SOURCE_OF_OMEGA_3_FATTY_ACIDS
labelClaimList.lclLabelClaim: EU Source of Omega-3 fatty acids
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is a source of omega-3 fatty acid and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer may only be made where the product contains at least 0.3 grams of acid to alpha-linolenic 100 g and 100 kcal or at least 40 mg of eicosapentaenoic acid and docosahexaenoic acid combined and 100 g per 100 kcal.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_OMEGA_3_FATTY_ACIDS
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in omega-3 fatty acid and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer may only be made where the product contains at least 0.6 grams of alpha-linolenic acid per 100 g and 100 kcal or at least 80 mg of eicosapentaenoic acid and docosahexaenoic acid combined to 100 g and 100 kcal.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_MONO_UNSATURATED_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in monounsaturated fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer, may only be made where the product contains at least 45% of fatty acids derived from monounsaturated fat and if energy from monounsaturated fats represents over 20% of the energy of the product.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_POLYUNSATURATED_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in polyunsaturated fat, and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer may only be made where the product contains at least 45% of fatty acids derived from polyunsaturated fat if energy from polyunsaturated fats represents over 20% of the energy of the product.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_UNSATURATED_FAT
labelClaimList.description: A claim that a food is high in unsaturated fat and any claim likely to have the same meaning for the consumer may only be made where the product contains at least 70% derived from fatty acids and unsaturated fats if energy from unsaturated fat is more than 20% of the energy of the product.

labelClaimList.name: EU_HIGH_IODINE
